255
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:42,000
Because this is all kind of blurry to me.

256
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Frankly, Miss Warden Ma'am,

257
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,000
I don't remember a single gosh darn thing about it.

258
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Name's Meow Meow.

259
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Damn, I couldn't hold it in.

260
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:57,000
Okay, Miss Ma'am? Miss Ma'am?

261
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Miss Ma'am Meow Meow.

262
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,000
That's what my-

263
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Your grandpappy always used to call you.

264
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,000
That's weird.

265
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:07,000
No, why would my grandpappy call me that?

266
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,000
I don't know.

267
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,000
He called me sweetest Meow Meow.

268
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
And how proud of you he'd be.

269
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,000
Very proud.

270
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,000
Putting the likes of you away.

271
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,000
Oh, well now see here.

272
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:21,000
Listen, Miss Ma'am Meow Meow.

273
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:27,000
I just think that someone of my stature-

274
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Very small.

275
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Stings, but yes, you're not wrong.

276
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:36,000
Against your awesomely trained guards.

277
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Uh huh.

278
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:42,000
Just doesn't seem like the story adds up.

279
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:46,000
Last I remember, I fell asleep in the woods after escape-

280
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:51,000
Going for a walk.

281
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,000
It doesn't seem like your story adds up either.

282
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Okay, listen.

283
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,000
Promise you gotta not tell anybody.

284
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Uh huh.

285
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,000
Oh, well that's not a promise.

286
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Miss Ma'am Meow Meow, this is super important.

287
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,000
Lives are at stake.

288
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,000
Look, you are a prisoner.

289
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,000
I am the warden.

290
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:08,000
If you tell me information, it can be used against you in a court of law.

291
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,000
Oh, you guys have the court system.

292
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Of course we do.

293
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,000
We're a highly established organization here.

294
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:18,000
What do you think, you just fell into the back of a smuggler's copter?

295
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,000
Did I?

296
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,000
No!

297
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,000
I believe I was smuggled here.

298
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,000
Did you see that courtyard?

299
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,000
I fell asleep in the woods and I woke up in your prison.

300
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,000
Well, I can't explain how that happened.

301
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:34,000
And you also stole and assaulted an officer of the law.

302
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:41,000
I stole an officer of the law?

303
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Words are important, Miss Ma'am Meow Meow.

304
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,000
You said you passed out in a forest.

305
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,000
I did.

306
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,000
What an exhaustion.

307
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,000
Where was this forest?

308
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,000
It was the high forest.

309
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:55,000
Five hundred miles away high forest.

310
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:57,000
Yeah.

311
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:00,000
You have no recollection of how you got to Neverwinter.

312
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,000
I don't recollect.

313
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,000
No recollecting.

314
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Hmm.

315
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,000
Now it sounds like you're in a bit of a predicament.

316
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,000
I don't know what I'm going to do with you.

317
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,000
Well, I'm no stabber.

318
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,000
I'm just saying.

319
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,000
I don't stab.

320
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,000
Nobody in no soft spots.

321
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:16,000
So you carry daggers but no stabbing.

322
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,000
All right.

323
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,000
They're just for show.

324
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,000
I'm going to think of what I can do with you.

325
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,000
You mean for me?

326
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,000
For you.

327
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,000
Slip of the tongue.

328
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,000
Sorry.

329
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,000
Same.

330
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,000
Very.

331
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,000
All right.

332
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,000
You know what?

333
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,000
I sure do appreciate you, you know.

334
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:36,000
Let me into your beautiful office.

335
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,000
Like really.

336
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,000
Who is your decorator?

337
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,000
Me.

338
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,000
Oh, God.

339
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,000
Brains, beauty, and talent.

340
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,000
Okay.

341
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:49,000
Should I just head back down to my cell then?

342
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,000
I would really love to just hang here for a while.

343
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,000
Like, are you busy?

344
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,000
That's not going to happen.

345
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,000
You play cards?

346
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:59,000
Delegation has to happen away from the prisoners.

347
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Guard!

348
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Officer Tangren opens the door and he comes back in and says,

349
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,000
Take this one away.

350
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:10,000
I'll call for him in a little while.

351
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:14,000
Thank you so much, Miss Ma'am Meow Meow.

352
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,000
Yes.

353
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,000
I appreciate you and everything you do here.

354
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,000
Thank you.

355
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:25,000
I'll take it under advisement.

356
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,000
As I walk out, I whisper to the officer,

357
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:32,000
I don't think she knows what that phrase means.

358
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,000
Yeah.

359
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,000
Keep walking.

360
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Hey, can I have a piggyback back?

361
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,000
No.

362
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,000
Oh, you thought about it though for a minute.

363
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,000
He pushes you forward.

364
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,000
You thought, just for a minute you thought about it.

365
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Only because you said piggyback back.

366
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,000
Yeah, back.

367
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,000
Back to my cell.

368
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,000
A piggyback back.

369
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,000
Get walking.

370
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,000
All right.

371
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Glim, you've had a restful night in the quarters that you are in

372
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:16,000
and you wake up to the sound of birdsong in the morning

373
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:19,000
and on the table that's in your room,

374
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:24,000
there is a warm bowl of what looks like an oatmeal

375
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:28,000
and a glass of water as well as a pitcher

376
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:32,000
and you are alone in your room.

377
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:39,000
Okay, well I'm going to eat my oatmeal, drink my water

378
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:45,000
and then head out to see if I can find Sirma or, you know, anybody.

379
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:48,000
I'm ready for my training montage.

380
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:52,000
You walk out to the main chapel

381
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:58,000
and you hear what sounds like wood chopping behind the chapel.

382
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:01,000
I go check it out.

383
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:06,000
Walking around you see Sirma wielding an axe,

384
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,000
chopping a large pile of wood.

385
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:13,000
She doesn't seem to hear you walking around.

386
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:16,000
Sirma?

387
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,000
Sirma?

388
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:21,000
She stops and she turns around and says, oh, you're awake.

389
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:24,000
You got breakfast?

390
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,000
I did. I'm ready to start.

391
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Do you want me to chop some wood?

392
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,000
I mean, absolutely.

393
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,000
Absolutely.

394
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,000
The more the merrier.

395
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,000
She hands you the axe.

396
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,000
I'm good at chopping wood.

397
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,000
I'm very big and strong.

398
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,000
Perfect.

399
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:40,000
That's just what I'm looking for is she's tiring on my old back

400
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,000
and she takes a step back and sits down

401
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:47,000
and she pulls out kind of a dried food ration

402
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:52,000
and starts eating that, just getting some energy back

403
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,000
and she says, how was your sleep?

404
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,000
I had a good sleep.

405
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,000
It feels good here.

406
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,000
Good. Good.

407
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,000
I'm glad.

408
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:06,000
Well, I appreciate the help right now.

409
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:09,000
Is there any questions that you came up with overnight

410
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:13,000
before we begin kind of figuring out your next steps?

411
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:16,000
Well, gosh, I think I have a million, you know?

412
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,000
Like, what do I need to do?

413
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,000
Where do I need to go?

414
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,000
What skills do I need to have before I go there?

415
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:24,000
How hard do you think it's going to be

416
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,000
to fight whatever the bad thing I'm going to have to fight is?

417
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,000
Do you think I'm going to make any friends while I'm here?

418
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,000
Do you think I'm going to make any friends

419
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,000
when we go somewhere else?

420
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
I have so many questions.

421
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,000
She smiles.

422
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:37,000
You're going to have to run down those again,

423
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:41,000
but we'll cover them as succinctly as we can.

424
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,000
I think I caught where you're going to need to go

425
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,000
and how hard it's going to be.

426
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,000
Yep.

427
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,000
That was two of them for sure.

428
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,000
Good. Perfect.

429
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,000
Yes.

430
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:55,000
Well, you're calling to Bahamut.

431
00:20:55,000 --> 00:21:02,000
Bahamut is one of what could be taken as a warrior's way.

432
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:11,000
How much experience do you have fighting or with conflict?

433
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:14,000
Well, I've done some training, you know,

434
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:17,000
like you do like in school and things,

435
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:22,000
but I wouldn't say I have a lot of experience with conflict.

436
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,000
I've never been in a fight

437
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,000
or I've barely been in an argument.

438
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Sounds delightful, your village,

439
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:33,000
everybody just getting along there.

440
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:39,000
Your calling or your goals could be,

441
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,000
they're different for everybody,

442
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:47,000
but in most cases they derive from going out

443
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:53,000
and upholding the values of Bahamut,

444
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:58,000
of the good and all that is right in the world.

445
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:01,000
And when you come across conflicts

446
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:07,000
or when you are pulled to or drawn to something that is not right,

447
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:11,000
doing your best to set that right.

448
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:18,000
That doesn't necessarily mean to swing a blade or to hurt anyone.

449
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:21,000
We definitely don't want that,

450
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:33,000
but conflict resolution is something that you might become very good at.

451
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:37,000
Your journey, it begins here.

452
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:44,000
The next step is quite a ways away.

453
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:47,000
I can give you as many tools as I can,

454
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:50,000
answer as many questions as I can,

455
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:59,000
but in order to truly take on the ownership of what you are to do,

456
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:05,000
you must travel to a very holy place.

457
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:11,000
That place is one of the birthplaces of your people,

458
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:14,000
of the Dragonborn,

459
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:18,000
and it's called Tymanther.

460
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:21,000
What will I find there?

461
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:25,000
Once you are ready to go there,

462
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:30,000
you will travel most likely to the capital,

463
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:32,000
Gerad-Themar,

464
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:35,000
find the citadel to Bahamut

465
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:39,000
and declare your oath to him.

466
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:42,000
Well, what do I do to need to be ready to go there?

467
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:45,000
That comes in many different forms.

468
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:53,000
For some, it is going out and finding wrongs and correcting them.

469
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:55,000
For others, it is...

470
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,000
I mean, that one pretty much sums it all up,

471
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:04,000
but the way you go about that comes in many different ways.

472
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:11,000
To get there, it is said that you will need help.

473
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:19,000
Unfortunately, I cannot travel with you that far and be that help.

474
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:27,000
There are two souls who have been tied to your cause.

475
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:31,000
They are in the opposite direction of where you need to be.

476
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:37,000
And who are they? Do you know them? Are they at a different temple? Are they...

477
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:44,000
They are not necessarily of Bahamut's faith.

478
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:51,000
They are souls who are trying to figure out their own cause and their own path as well.

479
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:59,000
And together, it is said that you three will find that way.

480
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:03,000
We do not know their names.

481
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:18,000
We do know that one has come to us in the form of a halfling who is on the run from something.

482
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:29,000
The other, a half-orc who is struggling to find his own light in this world.

483
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:36,000
How will I know them when I find them? Will I know them?

484
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:40,000
I feel like you'll have a sense.

485
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:52,000
Something will draw you to them to help them or to just find them when you get near to them.

486
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:59,000
We have heard word that they may be in the region of Neverwinter.

487
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:03,000
Have you traveled that far before?

488
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:06,000
No, I haven't really traveled anywhere ever before.

489
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:13,000
Well, you're on for a wild ride then, my dear.

490
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:19,000
How will I know what the right thing to do is?

491
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:30,000
When I'm out there in the world and I need to do the right thing, I need to shine Bahamut's light wherever I go and right wrongs.

492
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:39,000
I guess I always just assumed I would know how to do that, but haven't really had much opportunity to put that into work.

493
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:46,000
You seem to have a pure soul, Glim.

494
00:26:46,000 --> 00:27:02,000
From what your mothers have told me, you show every sign that the right decision comes naturally to you.

495
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:15,000
The saying, trust your gut, whatever feels right in the moment is probably going to be a safe bet for you specifically.

496
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:21,000
Well, what can I learn here before I have to go on this journey to Neverwinter?

497
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:25,000
We can work on some of your abilities with your war pick.

498
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:32,000
We always hope that conflict can be resolved without the need to brandish our weapons.

499
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:44,000
But sometimes, some people, it does not work to speak to them and to talk them down from their own causes that are hurting others.

500
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:52,000
I can also tell you that Bahamut is always with you.

501
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:55,000
Not necessarily in a physical sense, of course.

502
00:27:55,000 --> 00:28:10,000
But always there when you need extra guidance or when you feel like something isn't making sense to you and you don't know the right way, you can call to him.

503
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:21,000
And how do I do that? Out loud? Like, hey, Bahamut, really need your help figuring out what to do right now.

504
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:24,000
Or, you know, more internal.

505
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:35,000
Again, whatever feels right in the moment, if it feels right to call out, but internally could be done too in the form of a prayer.

506
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:38,000
So it's a choose-your-own-adventure sort of calling out.

507
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:40,000
It's a choose-your-own-adventure.

508
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:42,000
Bammie, Bammie, Bammie.

509
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:53,000
You have on you, yes, a symbol of Bahamut, yes?

510
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:56,000
Yes, I do have a symbol.

511
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,000
I've had it since I was a baby.

512
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:06,000
And I guess learning what I learned yesterday, maybe it came with me to the village when I appeared there when I was a baby.

